# Component Structure Guide

## Component Organization
Components are organized in the following structure:

### Layout Components
Located in `src/layout/`:
- [Header.tsx](mdc:src/layout/Header.tsx) - Main navigation header
- [Footer.tsx](mdc:src/layout/Footer.tsx) - Site footer
- [Sidebar.tsx](mdc:src/layout/Sidebar.tsx) - Navigation sidebar

### Page Components
Located in `src/pages/`:
- [Home.tsx](mdc:src/pages/Home.tsx) - Home page
- [Products.tsx](mdc:src/pages/Products.tsx) - Products listing
- [ProductDetail.tsx](mdc:src/pages/ProductDetail.tsx) - Individual product view
- [Cart.tsx](mdc:src/pages/Cart.tsx) - Shopping cart
- [Checkout.tsx](mdc:src/pages/Checkout.tsx) - Checkout process

### Reusable Components
Located in `src/components/`:
- [ProductCard.tsx](mdc:src/components/ProductCard.tsx) - Product display card
- [Button.tsx](mdc:src/components/Button.tsx) - Reusable button component
- [Input.tsx](mdc:src/components/Input.tsx) - Form input component
- [Modal.tsx](mdc:src/components/Modal.tsx) - Modal dialog component

## Component Guidelines
1. Each component should be in its own directory with its associated files
2. Use TypeScript for all components
3. Follow the naming convention: PascalCase for component files
4. Include proper type definitions for props
5. Use TailwindCSS for styling
6. Implement proper error boundaries where needed

